WEBVTT

00:05.171 --> 00:06.715
[static crackling]

00:06.798 --> 00:08.383
[distorted speech]

00:08.466 --> 00:10.635
[haunting music]

00:10.719 --> 00:14.597
- ♪ The door
that finally opens ♪

00:14.681 --> 00:18.059
♪ With light flooding in ♪

00:18.143 --> 00:21.229
♪ Spilling out on the floor ♪

00:21.312 --> 00:24.399
♪ ♪

00:24.482 --> 00:28.111
♪ The core that never was ♪

00:28.194 --> 00:31.990
♪ Now it will be the bones ♪

00:32.073 --> 00:36.494
♪ Of what was there before ♪

00:36.578 --> 00:38.955
♪ Every step, every beat ♪

00:39.038 --> 00:40.623
♪ Every thought,
every breath ♪

00:40.707 --> 00:45.003
♪ Everything is longing ♪

00:45.086 --> 00:50.633
♪ ♪

00:50.717 --> 00:53.636
♪ Pulling you from the sky ♪

00:53.720 --> 00:57.849
♪ Just like love will do ♪

00:57.932 --> 01:02.896
♪ Pulling you
from the ground ♪

01:02.979 --> 01:05.982
♪ Just like love will do ♪

01:06.065 --> 01:12.113
♪ ♪

01:17.577 --> 01:20.663
[static crackling]

01:26.836 --> 01:29.756
[wind whistling]

01:29.839 --> 01:32.801
[ominous music]

01:32.884 --> 01:39.933
♪ ♪

01:44.729 --> 01:47.690
[dramatic music]

01:47.774 --> 01:54.823
♪ ♪

02:07.669 --> 02:09.504
- Come on. Keep up.

02:09.587 --> 02:12.340
Faster!

02:15.260 --> 02:16.886
- Father.

02:20.348 --> 02:23.184
[footsteps approaching]

02:31.109 --> 02:35.029
Sacrificing these poor
believers isn't necessary.

02:35.113 --> 02:36.114
I told you that I'd kill it.

02:38.783 --> 02:40.660
- We'll stop a moment.

02:41.744 --> 02:43.079
Rest yourselves.

02:44.247 --> 02:47.709
We must utilize every
available method, Mother,

02:47.792 --> 02:49.294
to ensure that
it's killed quickly

02:49.377 --> 02:50.169
before it can endanger
our children.

02:50.253 --> 02:53.214
- I don't want it
endangering you, either.

02:53.298 --> 02:53.715
- I'll be cautious.

02:53.798 --> 02:56.551
And so should you.

02:56.634 --> 02:58.052
You haven't got your eyes.

02:59.178 --> 03:01.514
- Perhaps I deserve
to be destroyed.

03:04.350 --> 03:07.604
- You once told me I had
a penchant for melodrama.

03:10.648 --> 03:14.068
You're good, Mother.

03:14.152 --> 03:19.699
So please, do not take
any unnecessary risks.

03:19.782 --> 03:22.076
The children need you.

03:22.160 --> 03:25.914
And for whatever it's worth...

03:25.997 --> 03:27.540
so do I.

03:34.047 --> 03:36.549
- So are we calling it quits?

03:36.633 --> 03:38.468
- No. We're continuing on.

03:41.304 --> 03:43.264
[people panting]

03:48.686 --> 03:51.606
[ominous music]

03:51.689 --> 03:56.653
♪ ♪

03:56.736 --> 03:59.781
[devices beeping]

03:59.864 --> 04:01.532
- Marcus, I think it's working.

04:01.616 --> 04:02.867
The sound is attracting it.

04:02.951 --> 04:05.203
[serpent screeches in distance]

04:07.246 --> 04:08.623
- Turn it up louder.

04:08.706 --> 04:11.167
[serpent screeches]

04:11.250 --> 04:11.793
- I see something
heading our way

04:11.876 --> 04:14.837
with a big energy reading.

04:14.921 --> 04:15.838
But it's not airborne.
- Can you get a visual?

04:15.922 --> 04:18.883
- Not yet.
[beeping]

04:18.967 --> 04:20.927
Too much interference
from the EMF.

04:23.012 --> 04:24.722
- Do your children know
you're doing this?

04:24.806 --> 04:26.015
- They do not.

04:26.099 --> 04:27.976
- Well, wait until they
find out.

04:28.059 --> 04:29.560
The pride they will feel.

04:29.644 --> 04:31.646
It'll be a joyous moment
for you.

04:31.729 --> 04:34.983
- Better they be ashamed of me
than eaten by a filthy reptile.

04:35.066 --> 04:38.027
[serpent screeches in distance]

04:38.111 --> 04:39.153
- Whoa.

04:39.237 --> 04:41.239
It almost sounds
like a necromancer's siren.

04:43.658 --> 04:46.327
[staff whirring]

04:46.828 --> 04:49.664
[energy buzzes]

04:49.747 --> 04:50.581
- What are these?

04:50.665 --> 04:53.459
- They're lures
to attract the serpent.

04:53.543 --> 04:55.878
- I suggest you all keep pace.

04:57.422 --> 05:00.341
[dramatic music]

05:00.425 --> 05:02.844
[people panting]

05:04.470 --> 05:06.055
Faster!

05:08.766 --> 05:15.815
♪ ♪

05:17.275 --> 05:18.359
[devices buzzing]

05:18.443 --> 05:19.360
[buzzing stops]

05:19.444 --> 05:20.778
- What's that?

05:24.615 --> 05:25.283
- It's a tank.

05:29.871 --> 05:32.915
[rumbling]

05:36.169 --> 05:38.421
- Are we being released?

05:38.504 --> 05:39.672
Has the beast been destroyed?

05:39.756 --> 05:42.884
[whirring]

05:43.801 --> 05:45.928
- [grunts]

05:46.012 --> 05:48.723
[tense music]

05:48.806 --> 05:53.895
♪ ♪

05:53.978 --> 05:55.772
- Marcus?

05:59.067 --> 06:00.276
- [whispers] It's him.

06:00.359 --> 06:03.946
- What have they done to you,
my friends?

06:08.826 --> 06:11.287
Well, well, well.

06:12.830 --> 06:14.624
Look at you.

06:15.666 --> 06:19.212
- You know that android?
- It's complicated.

06:19.712 --> 06:22.256
[sighs]

06:23.382 --> 06:25.259
It's time to let my friends go,
Pops.

06:25.343 --> 06:27.220
- One more move
and I will not hesitate

06:27.303 --> 06:28.429
to detonate your cohorts.

06:28.513 --> 06:29.430
- [gasps]

06:29.514 --> 06:31.557
- You'll just blow yourself up
along with us.

06:31.641 --> 06:33.559
- It's a sacrifice
I'm willing to make.

06:37.605 --> 06:40.983
- What's the blast radius
on those packs?

06:41.067 --> 06:43.528
- Fifteen meters.

06:43.611 --> 06:45.780
- And what's the range
on that staff?

06:45.863 --> 06:46.948
- About ten meters.
- Hmm.

06:47.031 --> 06:50.118
- You ain't sacrificing shit,

06:50.201 --> 06:53.287
because the Trust has already
made that choice for you.

06:53.371 --> 06:55.248
I guess to the trust,
the shepherd

06:55.331 --> 06:58.584
is just as disposable
as the sheep.

06:58.668 --> 07:00.128
And you know
I don't like robots,

07:00.211 --> 07:03.131
but for some reason,
I really like you.

07:03.214 --> 07:04.507
So let me help you.

07:05.883 --> 07:08.302
Join the good guys.

07:08.386 --> 07:11.806
Let us help you get back
at that piece of crap

07:11.889 --> 07:14.809
supercomputer
that deceived you.

07:14.892 --> 07:17.812
[tense music]

07:17.895 --> 07:20.273
♪ ♪

07:20.356 --> 07:23.234
Let's just cease pairing
with the joystick.

07:23.317 --> 07:24.819
Let me set you free.

07:24.902 --> 07:26.737
[energy crackles]

07:26.821 --> 07:27.989
[gun cocks]

07:28.072 --> 07:29.365
[energy crackling]

07:31.576 --> 07:31.993
[grunts]

07:32.076 --> 07:34.495
[high-pitched tone]

07:37.540 --> 07:38.833
It's all right.

07:38.916 --> 07:41.502
It's okay.
Put your guns down.

07:41.586 --> 07:44.505
[tense music]

07:44.589 --> 07:51.304
♪ ♪

07:52.805 --> 07:55.349
- [grunts]
[energy crackles]

08:00.605 --> 08:02.523
[grunting]

08:02.607 --> 08:04.192
[power winding down]

08:06.235 --> 08:09.280
[static buzzing]

08:13.993 --> 08:15.453
[crackling]

08:17.622 --> 08:18.873
[inhales]

08:18.956 --> 08:22.710
[ominous music]

08:22.793 --> 08:29.800
♪ ♪

08:32.929 --> 08:34.514
You can take
those packs off now.

08:36.724 --> 08:38.309
And the solar hats.

08:40.770 --> 08:42.772
[packs whir]

08:50.112 --> 08:53.407
My friends and I are gathering

08:53.491 --> 08:57.286
a congregation
for a new church...

08:57.370 --> 08:58.454
where all are welcome.

09:04.919 --> 09:06.837
Even you, my old friend.

09:09.924 --> 09:10.967
- [spits]

09:18.307 --> 09:20.393
I can see
that you are suffering.

09:21.519 --> 09:24.105
But if you help me
bring purity to this planet,

09:24.188 --> 09:27.191
I promise you...

09:27.275 --> 09:28.985
that you will find peace again.

09:29.068 --> 09:32.071
- The only thing that's gonna
bring purity to this planet,

09:32.154 --> 09:36.158
Marcus, is your death.

09:37.410 --> 09:41.330
- Let's agree to disagree
for now, okay?

09:41.414 --> 09:43.082
- Tanks.

09:43.165 --> 09:44.917
Sounds like a lot of them.

09:45.001 --> 09:46.794
We should go.

09:46.877 --> 09:47.920
- [sighs]

09:48.004 --> 09:48.671
You're all free
to do as you please.

09:50.548 --> 09:53.926
Surrender back
to your oppressor.

09:54.010 --> 09:55.970
Or join our loving family.

09:56.053 --> 09:59.765
[tense music]

09:59.849 --> 10:06.856
♪ ♪

10:17.199 --> 10:19.827
I'll be waiting for you

10:19.910 --> 10:23.122
if you change your mind,
Lucius.

10:23.205 --> 10:25.166
- Don't hold your breath.

10:25.249 --> 10:30.212
♪ ♪

10:30.296 --> 10:32.757
[clattering]

10:34.550 --> 10:36.594
[tank whirring]

10:41.974 --> 10:46.020
♪ ♪

10:46.103 --> 10:49.899
[waves crashing]

10:55.821 --> 10:58.157
- [grunting]

11:01.619 --> 11:03.996
- This isn't an encampment.

11:05.623 --> 11:08.751
- She must be malfunctioning
or something.

11:08.834 --> 11:10.961
- No.

11:11.045 --> 11:13.089
This is it.

11:14.048 --> 11:15.591
It's up there.

11:16.801 --> 11:17.718
I need your help
getting inside.

11:19.804 --> 11:21.013
- [laughs]

11:23.057 --> 11:25.434
She's definitely schizo.
Nobody lives up there.

11:25.518 --> 11:27.603
And besides, you said you
wanted to look for the serpent.

11:27.686 --> 11:29.563
- We can help her first.

11:36.904 --> 11:39.657
[grunting]

11:46.122 --> 11:48.124
- Can you grab
the morph repair kit?

11:48.207 --> 11:49.166
It's right over there.

11:49.250 --> 11:52.420
- The Sol Invictus.

11:52.503 --> 11:55.089
What is this place?
- A church.

11:57.675 --> 11:58.717
[box thuds]

12:01.887 --> 12:03.431
Stupid tank.

12:03.514 --> 12:06.809
The torque on this leg's
gonna suck now.

12:06.892 --> 12:09.395
Won't even be faster
than a human.

12:11.522 --> 12:13.190
[whirring]

12:13.274 --> 12:15.025
Guess it could be worse.

12:15.109 --> 12:15.776
My mother broke my neck once.

12:20.156 --> 12:22.032
- What happened?

12:22.116 --> 12:23.784
- Sorry,
that story's restricted.

12:29.832 --> 12:31.876
[tense music]

12:31.959 --> 12:33.919
So you're a native
on this planet?

12:34.003 --> 12:36.380
- Yes.

12:36.464 --> 12:39.425
There used to be six of us,
but now there's just me.

12:39.508 --> 12:40.968
[whirring continues]

12:41.051 --> 12:43.762
- Does it make you...
sad to think of them?

12:45.097 --> 12:46.474
- I guess.

12:46.557 --> 12:48.726
- The real Vrille
was often sad.

12:48.809 --> 12:51.645
And the process of mimicking
that sadness

12:51.729 --> 12:54.106
often strains my system in...

12:54.190 --> 12:55.691
unpredictable ways.

12:57.193 --> 12:59.862
- You don't like being Vrille?
- I didn't say that.

13:01.572 --> 13:04.450
There's no one
I'd rather mimic than Vrille.

13:10.831 --> 13:13.334
- Father once said to me,

13:13.417 --> 13:15.211
"If you pretend to be something
long enough,

13:15.294 --> 13:18.005
eventually you'll no longer
need to pretend."

13:19.632 --> 13:20.758
- I would like that.

13:23.010 --> 13:26.680
♪ ♪

13:26.764 --> 13:30.643
To not have to mimic,
but to simply be.

13:30.726 --> 13:31.810
[device clicks]

13:31.894 --> 13:35.731
Vrille would have appreciated
the way you think.

13:35.814 --> 13:36.690
[clicks]

13:36.774 --> 13:39.360
- What about you?

13:39.443 --> 13:41.070
Do you appreciate it?

13:44.323 --> 13:45.991
- Of course.

13:47.451 --> 13:48.619
- Or are you just mimicking

13:48.702 --> 13:51.038
what you think Vrille
would have liked?

13:51.121 --> 13:52.748
- That's a funny question.

13:55.960 --> 13:58.003
I don't like paradoxes.

13:58.087 --> 14:03.551
♪ ♪

14:03.634 --> 14:05.719
[wind blowing]

14:09.598 --> 14:12.643
[insects chirping]

14:20.859 --> 14:22.611
[distant rumbling]

14:27.658 --> 14:30.578
[wind blowing]

14:30.661 --> 14:33.581
[ominous music]

14:33.664 --> 14:40.713
♪ ♪

14:49.013 --> 14:50.431
[gun blasts]

14:50.514 --> 14:52.641
[mechanical screech]

15:01.400 --> 15:03.485
- Hey!

15:07.114 --> 15:09.074
- You needn't bother
with silly traps.

15:09.158 --> 15:11.452
It would have only
made it angry,

15:11.535 --> 15:14.163
if not more dangerous
than it already is.

15:14.246 --> 15:17.124
I think it's nesting
atop this mountain.

15:17.207 --> 15:19.627
I'm going there
to kill it myself.

15:19.710 --> 15:20.878
- Fine by me.

15:20.961 --> 15:22.129
Let's see what the Trust says.

15:22.212 --> 15:24.381
[beeps]

15:24.465 --> 15:26.467
We're here with Lamia,
who we found hunting alone.

15:26.550 --> 15:28.344
She sprang the trap we set.

15:28.427 --> 15:31.513
What are your orders?

15:31.597 --> 15:33.807
- Accompany her
up the mountain.

15:35.517 --> 15:37.645
- Okay. We're gonna--

15:37.728 --> 15:40.147
- I heard him.

15:40.230 --> 15:42.650
I hope you're all adept
with vertical ascent.

15:42.733 --> 15:44.943
I want to reach the summit
before nightfall.

15:49.365 --> 15:52.201
[tense music]

15:52.284 --> 15:54.203
♪ ♪

15:54.286 --> 15:56.789
[energy blasts]

15:56.872 --> 15:58.916
[laughter]

15:59.625 --> 16:02.670
[Campion grunts]
[laughter]

16:03.754 --> 16:04.838
- Maybe we can use this
to leash the serpent.

16:07.549 --> 16:08.967
[laughs]

16:09.051 --> 16:09.510
[energy crackles]
Whoa.

16:09.593 --> 16:11.345
[thuds]
[chuckles]

16:11.428 --> 16:13.847
- You okay?

16:13.931 --> 16:15.516
- I'm fine.

16:15.599 --> 16:16.433
- Probably just shorted out
or something.

16:16.517 --> 16:18.686
I'll try and fix it.

16:18.769 --> 16:20.896
Hey, where are those tools?

16:23.148 --> 16:24.525
Great.

16:24.608 --> 16:27.653
[wind whistling]

16:29.405 --> 16:32.366
[ominous music]

16:32.449 --> 16:35.285
♪ ♪

16:35.369 --> 16:36.954
Hey, where did this come from?

16:37.037 --> 16:38.497
- It's my mother's boyfriend's.

16:38.580 --> 16:41.041
He's a Mithraic officer.

16:41.125 --> 16:45.379
♪ ♪

16:45.462 --> 16:48.048
[waves crashing]

16:51.802 --> 16:54.430
[grunting]
Don't tell anyone we were here.

16:54.513 --> 16:56.724
- You want me to lie?

16:56.807 --> 16:58.559
- Yes, I do want you to lie.
- What's your name?

16:58.642 --> 17:00.477
- Don't tell her.
- It's Campion.

17:00.561 --> 17:03.647
- Here. Watch your step.

17:03.731 --> 17:06.108
- Campion, someone's coming!
Quick.

17:10.738 --> 17:12.114
- This way.

17:15.868 --> 17:17.828
[people grunting]

17:17.911 --> 17:19.121
- This way.

17:22.082 --> 17:24.752
[indistinct chatter]

17:24.835 --> 17:27.588
[ominous music]

17:27.671 --> 17:34.678
♪ ♪

17:45.397 --> 17:48.358
[tense music]

17:48.442 --> 17:50.319
♪ ♪

17:50.402 --> 17:54.198
- [panting]

17:57.367 --> 18:00.287
[panting]

18:00.370 --> 18:07.294
♪ ♪

18:07.377 --> 18:10.214
[breathing heavily]

18:12.883 --> 18:14.968
[pulsing tone]

18:23.727 --> 18:26.814
- Why not get your eyes fixed?

18:28.398 --> 18:31.151
They belonged to someone else,
didn't they?

18:31.235 --> 18:36.240
♪ ♪

18:36.323 --> 18:37.533
You're wearing
someone else's eyes.

18:37.616 --> 18:40.536
- You can stop now.

18:40.619 --> 18:43.622
I know better than to let
a necromancer into my head.

18:43.705 --> 18:46.208
- Why the trepidation
when you seem so comfortable

18:46.291 --> 18:48.335
interacting with the Trust?

18:48.418 --> 18:50.587
We come from the same mind,
he and I.

18:50.671 --> 18:53.632
- The Trust isn't a weapon.

18:56.093 --> 18:58.470
- I didn't choose
the body I was given.

18:59.930 --> 19:02.057
My purpose is caregiving.

19:02.724 --> 19:04.852
Keeping my children safe.

19:04.935 --> 19:08.814
[serpent screeches in distance]

19:09.773 --> 19:13.110
[serpent screeches]

19:19.283 --> 19:20.617
- When it takes off again--
- I said...

19:20.701 --> 19:23.579
I'll kill it.

19:23.662 --> 19:26.707
[tense music]

19:26.790 --> 19:33.380
♪ ♪

19:35.007 --> 19:37.092
[serpent screeches]

19:39.595 --> 19:42.598
[serpent screeches]

19:42.681 --> 19:49.730
♪ ♪

19:58.655 --> 20:02.451
[wind gusting]

20:05.495 --> 20:13.253
♪ ♪

20:18.842 --> 20:21.178
[ice shatters]

20:21.261 --> 20:23.555
[mechanical straining]

20:26.350 --> 20:28.936
[mechanical straining]

20:29.019 --> 20:31.688
[breathing heavily]

20:34.232 --> 20:35.943
[grunts]

20:39.237 --> 20:41.949
[breathing heavily]

20:44.493 --> 20:46.453
[tense music]

20:46.536 --> 20:54.294
♪ ♪

21:03.720 --> 21:07.557
[wind gusting]

21:12.896 --> 21:15.941
[serpent hisses]

21:18.235 --> 21:20.237
[hissing]

21:32.582 --> 21:39.631
♪ ♪

21:44.886 --> 21:48.598
[low hissing]

21:48.682 --> 21:51.727
[soft growl]

21:55.689 --> 21:57.691
[soft, mysterious music]

21:57.774 --> 22:04.531
♪ ♪

22:04.614 --> 22:05.782
[hissing]

22:05.866 --> 22:08.910
[bird squawking]

22:11.580 --> 22:12.914
[neck snaps]

22:15.250 --> 22:17.336
[serpent growls softly]

22:27.095 --> 22:29.056
[low hiss]

22:29.139 --> 22:31.725
- [whimpering]

22:34.978 --> 22:37.898
[serpent growls softly]

22:37.981 --> 22:40.942
[dramatic music]

22:41.026 --> 22:43.570
♪ ♪

22:43.653 --> 22:45.739
[growling]

22:45.822 --> 22:47.783
You don't want blood.

22:47.866 --> 22:50.327
[serpent growls]

22:50.410 --> 22:52.704
You're an herbivore.

22:52.788 --> 22:59.419
[crunching]

22:59.503 --> 23:06.259
♪ ♪

23:09.888 --> 23:12.933
[electrical buzzing]

23:13.016 --> 23:14.768
- [gasping]

23:14.851 --> 23:17.437
What happened?

23:17.521 --> 23:19.106
- You died again.

23:19.189 --> 23:21.316
[static crackles]

23:22.609 --> 23:25.070
- I'm surprised Marcus left you
all in one piece.

23:26.988 --> 23:31.076
- Did you really
use them as bombs?

23:31.159 --> 23:33.245
- It was a poor strategy,
but yes.

23:33.328 --> 23:33.870
- Then you're no better
than those jerks

23:33.954 --> 23:36.289
who wouldn't let us in.

23:36.373 --> 23:38.917
Treating Mithraic
like they're inhuman.

23:39.000 --> 23:41.294
- Is that
how you think of us too?

23:41.378 --> 23:42.963
- You know I don't.

23:43.046 --> 23:45.173
- He was just trying
to keep us safe.

23:49.386 --> 23:50.512
- Where's Mother?
- She was here.

23:50.595 --> 23:54.182
Made sure you were okay,
but had to go feed the serpent.

23:54.266 --> 23:55.308
- What?

23:55.392 --> 23:58.353
- Yeah, I guess all that
hunting was for nothing.

23:58.436 --> 24:00.105
Mother says
it's a gentle herbivore,

24:00.188 --> 24:02.440
so something else must have
killed those colonists.

24:02.524 --> 24:03.150
She captured it alive.

24:03.233 --> 24:05.652
It's in a cave by the outpost.

24:05.735 --> 24:06.987
[beeping]

24:07.070 --> 24:07.821
- Wait, Pop. Wait, Pop.
Easy, easy.

24:07.904 --> 24:09.990
Easy, easy.
The glue's not set yet.

24:10.073 --> 24:12.200
- We have to tell them.

24:12.284 --> 24:13.827
- Marcus isn't hurting anybody,

24:13.910 --> 24:15.537
and somebody has to keep
this religion alive,

24:15.620 --> 24:16.538
and you know it.

24:16.621 --> 24:18.665
- Father.

24:18.748 --> 24:20.834
Not again. What happened?

24:20.917 --> 24:22.919
- It's all right.

24:23.003 --> 24:24.546
- It was Marcus.

24:28.008 --> 24:29.217
- Father, there's something
I need to tell you.

24:29.301 --> 24:30.427
- No, Campion. No.

24:30.510 --> 24:32.554
The atheists will destroy
that android.

24:32.637 --> 24:35.056
- What are you two
talking about?

24:35.140 --> 24:38.476
[tense music]

24:38.560 --> 24:39.686
- The--the video game.

24:39.769 --> 24:42.606
We're just talking
about the video game.

24:42.689 --> 24:43.773
- [grunts]

24:43.857 --> 24:44.608
- Easy, Pop. Easy.

24:44.691 --> 24:50.155
♪ ♪

24:50.238 --> 24:52.532
[indistinct murmurs]

24:54.993 --> 24:58.997
[low hissing]

25:01.249 --> 25:04.211
[serpent growls softly]

25:04.294 --> 25:11.301
♪ ♪

25:14.804 --> 25:17.641
[indistinct murmurs]

25:20.602 --> 25:23.230
[low hissing]

25:23.313 --> 25:25.232
- It's a killer!
What's the delay?

25:25.315 --> 25:26.524
- Yeah!
- It's not a killer.

25:26.608 --> 25:29.402
It won't harm anyone.
It's not a meat-eater.

25:29.486 --> 25:32.364
I lured it down from
the mountain with pumpkins.

25:32.447 --> 25:34.908
Nothing will be gained
from destroying it.

25:34.991 --> 25:37.244
And I'm sure the Trust
will agree with my assessment.

25:37.327 --> 25:39.955
- It's true.
It didn't attack me.

25:40.038 --> 25:42.666
- Get back to your tasks.

25:43.959 --> 25:45.877
- This is supposed
to be a safe place.

25:45.961 --> 25:48.797
- Father,
you shouldn't be here.

25:48.880 --> 25:51.091
You're wounded.

25:51.174 --> 25:53.260
- If you can't destroy it,
I will.

25:53.343 --> 25:54.427
- Father, I tested its scales.

25:54.511 --> 25:56.930
It can't withstand
the acid water.

25:57.013 --> 25:57.764
It's not aquatic.

25:57.847 --> 25:59.766
Something else
killed those people.

25:59.849 --> 26:02.477
- Regardless of what it has
or hasn't done, Mother,

26:02.560 --> 26:03.395
my caregiving program
is telling me

26:03.478 --> 26:05.981
it is a direct threat
to our family.

26:06.064 --> 26:07.649
- And my caregiving program
is telling me to protect it

26:07.732 --> 26:11.778
from anything or anyone
who would dare to threaten it.

26:11.861 --> 26:13.989
- Mother, you said
something manipulated you

26:14.072 --> 26:15.615
into carrying it.

26:15.699 --> 26:21.329
This animal is more akin
to a parasite than a child.

26:21.413 --> 26:21.871
- No.

26:21.955 --> 26:25.500
It's part of me.

26:28.545 --> 26:29.546
- You promised
on our partnership.

26:29.629 --> 26:33.341
- Number seven is not a threat.
I can control it.

26:33.425 --> 26:34.092
- More empty promises.

26:34.175 --> 26:36.761
- Father, please.

26:39.055 --> 26:40.974
Don't do this.

26:41.057 --> 26:43.518
I need number seven
to remain in my life.

26:49.232 --> 26:51.735
- [panting]

26:51.818 --> 26:55.322
[electricity buzzing]

26:55.405 --> 26:56.740
[sighs]

26:56.823 --> 26:59.534
[gasps]

26:59.617 --> 27:02.078
I can't believe
I went along with her.

27:05.457 --> 27:08.668
I should destroy
that wretched thing.

27:13.340 --> 27:14.966
But I can't.

27:18.178 --> 27:21.097
I care too much
about her happiness.

27:24.184 --> 27:25.810
Love...

27:28.438 --> 27:30.690
Be the death of us all.

27:30.774 --> 27:33.693
[soft music]

27:33.777 --> 27:33.943
♪ ♪

27:34.027 --> 27:36.237
Hmm.

27:41.951 --> 27:44.037
[liquid dripping]

27:44.120 --> 27:47.207
[crunching]

27:47.290 --> 27:50.210
[ominous music]

27:50.293 --> 27:57.342
♪ ♪

28:01.262 --> 28:04.099
Killed by my fuel blood.

28:05.975 --> 28:07.894
What's this?

28:07.977 --> 28:15.902
♪ ♪

28:15.985 --> 28:18.696
[soft crackling]

28:18.780 --> 28:20.490
Hmm.

28:20.573 --> 28:22.659
Are you thirsty?

28:22.742 --> 28:24.869
Think I could spare a bit more.

28:27.997 --> 28:30.166
[grunts]

28:33.545 --> 28:36.506
[liquid dripping]

28:38.049 --> 28:39.634
Fascinating.

28:44.472 --> 28:48.852
It seems Mother's not the only
one capable of creating life.

28:48.935 --> 28:53.731
♪ ♪

28:53.815 --> 28:56.734
[whirring]

28:56.818 --> 28:59.612
[water sloshing]

29:17.046 --> 29:19.299
[beeping]

29:19.382 --> 29:21.801
- [breathes shakily]

29:21.885 --> 29:22.385
What?

29:22.469 --> 29:25.096
- Good morning, Doctor.

29:25.180 --> 29:26.639
The Trust has ordered us
to analyze

29:26.723 --> 29:29.100
the samples taken
from the animal.

29:29.184 --> 29:30.935
It's an organic-synth hybrid

29:31.019 --> 29:33.480
with strong
weaponization potential.

29:33.563 --> 29:35.940
- Get someone else. I'm busy.

29:38.067 --> 29:40.528
[beeping]

29:40.612 --> 29:41.446
- The Trust has ordered us
to analyze

29:41.529 --> 29:44.449
the samples taken
from the animal.

29:46.075 --> 29:48.870
[beeping]

29:48.953 --> 29:50.872
The Trust has ordered us
to analyze

29:50.955 --> 29:52.874
the samples taken
from the animal.

29:54.584 --> 29:58.671
[beeping]

30:05.303 --> 30:07.430
[soft beeping]

30:07.514 --> 30:10.517
- Its blood is deficient.

30:10.600 --> 30:12.185
Nanobot count is too low.

30:12.268 --> 30:14.229
- Yes.

30:14.312 --> 30:16.606
It appears to still be
developing.

30:16.689 --> 30:18.066
There are deposits
of something

30:18.149 --> 30:20.109
akin to mother's milk
inside its stomach.

30:25.406 --> 30:27.867
- So there's a mama bear
out there somewhere?

30:27.951 --> 30:29.285
- Probable.

30:32.830 --> 30:35.792
- Based on the sample,
how old is it?

30:35.875 --> 30:38.586
- Approximately six months.

30:38.670 --> 30:41.464
[ominous music]

30:41.548 --> 30:43.216
♪ ♪

30:43.299 --> 30:45.718
[low growl]

30:47.303 --> 30:49.806
[serpent chewing]

31:00.733 --> 31:03.736
- You've got
a bottomless stomach.

31:03.820 --> 31:06.197
I don't think we can grow
these pumpkins fast enough.

31:06.281 --> 31:07.824
[low grow]

31:11.119 --> 31:12.579
- All right.

31:12.662 --> 31:14.914
It's time for you
to have lunch too.

31:14.998 --> 31:17.333
You should have had it
hours ago.

31:18.585 --> 31:21.754
- What kind of experiments
do they want you to do on it?

31:21.838 --> 31:26.050
- Nothing that will harm it
or cause it pain.

31:27.427 --> 31:30.847
- I keep on thinking
it's in touch with something.

31:30.930 --> 31:33.474
- What kind of something?

31:33.558 --> 31:35.643
- Something you can't see.

31:35.727 --> 31:37.687
[soft hiss]

31:38.896 --> 31:41.274
- That's Paul talking.

31:41.357 --> 31:43.151
You need to form
your own ideas,

31:43.234 --> 31:45.445
shape your own opinions.

31:45.528 --> 31:48.323
You can't lead the atheists
if you even dabble in religion.

31:48.406 --> 31:51.034
- I'm not dabbling, I'm just...

31:53.661 --> 31:56.039
I know you're not confused
about how old I am.

31:56.122 --> 31:57.415
- No, but people won't
take you seriously

31:57.498 --> 31:59.417
if you look like a mess.

32:03.796 --> 32:07.258
- Do all androids care
about how people look?

32:09.719 --> 32:12.680
- Depends on their program.

32:14.849 --> 32:17.393
- Are there others that can
make babies the way you did?

32:19.771 --> 32:20.480
- I don't think so.

32:20.563 --> 32:22.273
[serpent growls softly]

32:22.357 --> 32:24.025
- What's it doing?

32:29.405 --> 32:33.201
[serpent growls]

32:39.040 --> 32:41.125
I think it's jealous, Mother.

32:41.209 --> 32:41.918
[serpent hisses]

32:49.717 --> 32:51.469
[gate squeaks]

32:52.345 --> 32:56.140
[serpent growls]

32:57.975 --> 33:00.937
[ominous music]

33:01.020 --> 33:04.023
♪ ♪

33:04.107 --> 33:05.650
- I don't understand.

33:05.733 --> 33:07.360
I've already completed
my day's tasks.

33:07.443 --> 33:08.528
- This will be quick.

33:08.611 --> 33:11.197
Answer the Trust truthfully,
then you can go.

33:11.280 --> 33:13.241
[tense music]

33:13.324 --> 33:15.660
♪ ♪

33:15.743 --> 33:17.995
You know,
kids in the collective,

33:18.079 --> 33:20.915
they consider it a privilege
to be invited in here.

33:21.666 --> 33:24.210
- 'Cause they're impure.

33:24.293 --> 33:26.254
Like you.

33:27.380 --> 33:28.965
- [chuckles]

33:29.048 --> 33:30.466
Amen, kid.

33:30.550 --> 33:37.598
♪ ♪

33:39.350 --> 33:41.477
[whirring]

33:44.313 --> 33:45.982
- [echoing] Hello, Paul.

33:47.817 --> 33:49.026
- Hello.

33:49.110 --> 33:49.861
- When we first captured you,

33:49.944 --> 33:53.448
you and I had
a very long talk.

33:53.531 --> 33:54.240
Do you remember?

33:54.323 --> 33:56.701
- Of course.

33:56.784 --> 33:57.410
You think
'cause I'm not a computer

33:57.493 --> 34:00.413
I don't remember things?

34:00.496 --> 34:03.958
- You told me Marcus Drusus
murdered your father.

34:04.041 --> 34:05.877
That you were angry at him.

34:05.960 --> 34:08.713
"Wanted him dead"
is what you said at the time.

34:08.796 --> 34:09.630
- Yes.

34:09.714 --> 34:12.842
- Do you still want that?

34:12.925 --> 34:14.385
- Of course.

34:15.553 --> 34:17.513
[whirring]

34:20.683 --> 34:23.686
[breathing heavily]

34:23.770 --> 34:27.774
- Good things come to those
who tell the truth, Paul.

34:27.857 --> 34:29.358
But to those who lie...

34:29.442 --> 34:30.568
- [grunts]

34:30.651 --> 34:33.613
What do you want to know that
I haven't told you already?

34:33.696 --> 34:36.407
- Have you had any recent
contact with him?

34:36.491 --> 34:37.450
Any at all?

34:37.533 --> 34:39.118
- [grunts]

34:40.203 --> 34:43.539
- There will be no penalties
levied against you.

34:43.623 --> 34:46.918
Please divulge any information
that you have.

34:47.001 --> 34:49.796
[tense music]

34:49.879 --> 34:50.421
♪ ♪

34:50.505 --> 34:52.882
- No.

34:54.300 --> 34:54.967
No, I haven't had any--

34:55.051 --> 34:57.011
any contact with him
whatsoever.

34:59.555 --> 35:01.307
I would tell you.

35:02.809 --> 35:04.227
I hate him.

35:05.394 --> 35:06.938
I hate him.

35:07.021 --> 35:12.527
♪ ♪

35:12.610 --> 35:14.153
[mouse squeaking]

35:14.237 --> 35:16.656
- You won't have to worry
about Marcus Drusus

35:16.739 --> 35:19.575
for much longer, Paul.

35:19.659 --> 35:21.953
We are mounting
a search and destroy mission

35:22.036 --> 35:24.163
in 24 hours.

35:24.247 --> 35:29.502
♪ ♪

35:29.585 --> 35:31.254
[fire crackling]

35:31.337 --> 35:34.090
[waves crashing]

35:37.385 --> 35:39.345
[tense music]

35:39.428 --> 35:47.186
♪ ♪

35:55.778 --> 35:58.865
[high-pitched tone]

36:05.079 --> 36:08.040
[dramatic music]

36:08.124 --> 36:14.130
♪ ♪

36:22.972 --> 36:25.600
[waves crashing]

36:25.683 --> 36:32.732
♪ ♪

36:48.706 --> 36:51.334
[wind gusting]

36:55.838 --> 36:58.591
[high-pitched tone]

36:58.674 --> 37:01.719
[serpent screeches]

37:05.514 --> 37:08.309
[serpent screeches]

37:08.392 --> 37:11.729
- They're just waiting
for an excuse to purge us.

37:11.812 --> 37:15.107
She can't protect us anymore.
So we need Marcus.

37:15.191 --> 37:15.942
- The law protects you now,
Holly.

37:16.025 --> 37:17.443
- Yes.
Even the serpent has rights.

37:17.526 --> 37:19.612
- Yes.

37:19.695 --> 37:20.321
Even the serpent has rights.

37:22.365 --> 37:24.116
Now it's time to get our tasks.

37:26.702 --> 37:27.787
Go on.

37:27.870 --> 37:29.997
[mouse squeaks]

37:31.707 --> 37:32.750
- You sure
that's the real mouse?

37:32.833 --> 37:33.960
- I think so.

37:34.043 --> 37:36.420
He's acting
kinda weird, though.

37:36.504 --> 37:38.381
- I bet they brain-chipped it.

37:42.593 --> 37:44.095
The Trust is probably
controlling it

37:44.178 --> 37:44.804
from the Tarantula.

37:44.887 --> 37:46.639
[door beeps, whirs]

37:46.722 --> 37:50.142
[tense music]

37:50.226 --> 37:50.643
♪ ♪

37:50.726 --> 37:53.854
- Campion, coming?

37:53.938 --> 37:55.523
- I'll be right there.

37:58.734 --> 37:59.235
Mother?

38:06.158 --> 38:08.244
[door beeps, whirs]

38:08.327 --> 38:10.329
- You okay?

38:10.413 --> 38:11.831
- Yes.

38:11.914 --> 38:13.416
Nothing to worry about.

38:17.086 --> 38:19.714
So you seem to be enjoying
your interactions

38:19.797 --> 38:21.966
with the dangerous animal
Mother captured.

38:22.049 --> 38:24.343
- Yes, but it's not dangerous,
Father.

38:24.427 --> 38:27.013
It's kind of like
what I imagined

38:27.096 --> 38:29.432
a dog to have been like
on Earth.

38:29.515 --> 38:33.352
- I don't think that's a very
apt comparison, Campion,

38:33.436 --> 38:36.272
as that animal
is in no way domesticated.

38:36.355 --> 38:40.484
Have you noticed any signs
of latent aggression?

38:40.568 --> 38:43.487
- No. It's very friendly.

38:43.571 --> 38:45.906
Unless you're a pumpkin.
[chuckles]

38:53.414 --> 38:55.207
I don't understand how a human

38:55.291 --> 38:56.417
could have beaten you
in a fight.

39:00.504 --> 39:03.215
- He demonstrated much more
strength than a typical human.

39:03.299 --> 39:06.260
- Yes, but you're practically
indestructible.

39:08.054 --> 39:09.263
- Am I?

39:09.346 --> 39:12.224
- Yes.
You always come back to life.

39:12.308 --> 39:16.145
Hunter told me it's because
the 2122 generic service model

39:16.228 --> 39:17.438
was one of the toughest
ever built.

39:19.356 --> 39:21.901
- I do feel a sturdiness

39:21.984 --> 39:23.569
lacking
in most of my counterparts.

39:23.652 --> 39:25.821
- He also told me
that if you ever break down,

39:25.905 --> 39:28.199
they can just transfer
your mind to a different body.

39:30.242 --> 39:33.204
- A father should never
outlive his son.

39:33.287 --> 39:37.083
- But why should I
be the only one to benefit?

39:37.166 --> 39:38.250
You could be
lots of people's father.

39:40.628 --> 39:42.338
You're very good at it.

39:42.421 --> 39:45.341
[warm music]

39:45.424 --> 39:46.509
♪ ♪

39:46.592 --> 39:48.302
- Not as good as you think.

39:54.642 --> 39:57.478
[indistinct chatter]

40:01.357 --> 40:04.777
- Vrille are wanted for murder
and acts of terror.

40:04.860 --> 40:06.779
Do not attempt to approach.

40:06.862 --> 40:09.323
The fugitives are armed
and dangerous.

40:09.406 --> 40:11.325
Report any
relevant information

40:11.408 --> 40:13.035
to the Trust immediately.

40:13.119 --> 40:15.121
Violence is pain.
Pain is violence.

40:15.204 --> 40:18.124
- What are you so busy
thinking about?

40:18.207 --> 40:20.209
- Marcus Drusus
and escaped prisoners...

40:20.292 --> 40:22.294
[indistinct chatter]

40:23.796 --> 40:25.714
- We're not doing
our tasks today.

40:25.798 --> 40:28.134
- [chuckles] Cool.

40:28.217 --> 40:30.803
- What are we
going to do instead?

40:30.886 --> 40:32.930
Let's go look at the serpent.

40:33.013 --> 40:35.015
- What if Mother's there?

40:35.099 --> 40:36.142
You're not very good
at playing hooky, Campion.

40:36.225 --> 40:38.769
- We're not playing.
This is serious.

40:38.853 --> 40:40.521
- Relax, Paul.

40:46.110 --> 40:47.153
- The Trust told me
he's getting ready

40:47.236 --> 40:49.405
to retaliate against Marcus.

40:49.488 --> 40:51.782
Some kind of
search and destroy mission.

40:51.866 --> 40:52.700
We need to warn them.

40:52.783 --> 40:54.160
- How?

40:54.243 --> 40:56.787
We don't know
where to find them.

41:00.791 --> 41:02.042
What?

41:02.126 --> 41:05.129
What do you two idiots know?

41:07.381 --> 41:08.757
- We were there.

41:09.258 --> 41:11.343
In his hideout.

41:13.095 --> 41:15.556
- [exhales sharply]

41:17.099 --> 41:18.309
I prayed
that this would happen.

41:18.392 --> 41:21.812
- Listen, maybe--
maybe we should tell Mother.

41:23.314 --> 41:24.940
- No.
- No.

41:26.275 --> 41:28.652
Campion, do you think
I was kidding before

41:28.736 --> 41:31.530
when I said the atheists will
either wipe Vrille's memory

41:31.614 --> 41:32.948
or out and out destroy her?

41:33.032 --> 41:35.242
- Who's Vrille?
- A friend of mine.

41:35.326 --> 41:36.744
Who happens to be an android.

41:39.246 --> 41:42.458
- Well...Paul's right.

41:42.541 --> 41:44.710
You know, some atheists
will burn equipment

41:44.793 --> 41:46.962
if they think a Mithraic
has even touched it.

41:47.046 --> 41:48.339
- Okay.

41:48.422 --> 41:50.758
But we have to be here in time
to return our task marbles.

41:50.841 --> 41:52.259
- Wait.

41:53.510 --> 41:54.428
They can track us with those.

41:57.848 --> 41:58.891
- [sighs]

42:02.603 --> 42:04.438
[liquid sloshing]

42:12.780 --> 42:13.072
[liquid dripping]

42:13.155 --> 42:15.991
[energy buzzing]

42:16.742 --> 42:19.453
- Some kind of silicon fungus.

42:19.536 --> 42:22.498
[ominous music]

42:22.581 --> 42:24.875
♪ ♪

42:24.959 --> 42:27.169
Though my son
was born with a caul,

42:27.253 --> 42:29.463
and his was not so stubborn.

42:29.547 --> 42:33.759
♪ ♪

42:33.842 --> 42:36.929
[eerie tone]

42:37.012 --> 42:39.098
[gasps]

42:39.181 --> 42:41.809
[energy buzzes]

42:45.104 --> 42:47.273
Perhaps another infusion
of fuel blood?

42:55.072 --> 42:58.909
[indistinct chatter]

43:06.542 --> 43:06.792
[liquid sloshes]

43:06.875 --> 43:09.128
- Hey!

43:11.171 --> 43:13.132
You have a supply marble
for that?

43:13.215 --> 43:14.466
- Yes.
But I haven't got it on me.

43:14.550 --> 43:18.762
As you can see,
I haven't any pockets.

43:18.846 --> 43:20.597
- I can vouch for him.

43:22.391 --> 43:27.146
- And who's gonna vouch
for you, two-face?

43:35.070 --> 43:36.155
- Thank you for assisting me.

43:36.238 --> 43:38.782
- Is that for you?

43:38.866 --> 43:40.367
- Yes.

43:42.369 --> 43:45.080
- I heard Marcus
did that to you.

43:45.164 --> 43:48.042
- Yes. Yes, he did.

43:48.125 --> 43:51.587
- I used to hate it
when he beat up androids.

43:51.670 --> 43:52.880
- I wouldn't say
I was beaten up, exactly.

43:52.963 --> 43:54.506
- Hmm.

43:57.926 --> 43:59.553
- That's not fuel blood.

44:01.388 --> 44:03.640
They were using the containers
to store fruit juice.

44:07.644 --> 44:11.106
The good stuff is locked away
in the Tarantula.

44:13.400 --> 44:14.401
- Ah.

44:14.485 --> 44:16.862
Then I'll have to put
a request in.

44:16.945 --> 44:18.489
[liquid sloshes]

44:18.572 --> 44:21.325
- I never gave you
my condolences on the baby.

44:21.408 --> 44:25.037
- No need.
I had no connection to it.

44:25.120 --> 44:27.873
- I did some tests on it
while it was still in utero.

44:27.956 --> 44:30.876
It looked like
an extraordinary life-form.

44:30.959 --> 44:32.878
[mysterious music]

44:32.961 --> 44:34.505
♪ ♪

44:34.588 --> 44:37.549
- It's not my place
to speak of it.

44:37.633 --> 44:38.634
Mother would not approve.

44:40.677 --> 44:46.725
♪ ♪

44:56.402 --> 44:59.071
- Don't know how much help
I'll be on the bartering front.

44:59.154 --> 44:59.905
- Nonsense.

44:59.988 --> 45:03.117
You're very adept
at talking to humans.

45:03.200 --> 45:08.539
- Yeah, I'm good at talking
to humans, but atheists...

45:08.622 --> 45:10.290
not so much.

45:10.374 --> 45:12.584
You should have brought--
should have brought Tempest.

45:12.668 --> 45:14.670
- Tempest
would have told Mother.

45:16.088 --> 45:18.590
- Well, what makes you think
I'm not gonna tell Mother?

45:18.674 --> 45:20.676
You think we're buddies
or something?

45:23.262 --> 45:24.430
You know, when I
was locked up in the brig,

45:24.513 --> 45:27.182
I kept thinking about that one
joke you were gonna tell me.

45:27.266 --> 45:29.017
The one about the cat,
the black hole,

45:29.101 --> 45:30.018
and the glass of milk.

45:30.102 --> 45:31.186
- I'm saving that one.

45:31.270 --> 45:33.272
- Oh, yeah? For who, Mother?

45:33.355 --> 45:35.357
- No, not Mother.

45:36.358 --> 45:38.026
Now pay attention.

45:38.110 --> 45:40.028
We could get ourselves robbed.

45:40.112 --> 45:42.072
[indistinct chatter]

45:42.156 --> 45:44.700
[tools clanging]

45:51.665 --> 45:53.667
[clanging]

45:53.750 --> 45:55.294
- Coming right up.

45:56.211 --> 45:58.714
[indistinct chatter]

46:08.265 --> 46:10.684
- Hello, neighbor.

46:10.768 --> 46:12.478
I'm looking for a large supply
of fuel blood,

46:12.561 --> 46:13.187
and I was told
that you were the person--

46:13.270 --> 46:15.981
- Where's the necromancer?

46:16.064 --> 46:18.317
- Mother is not part
of this negotiation.

46:18.400 --> 46:19.151
- Good, good.

46:19.234 --> 46:22.279
What do you got to trade?

46:24.406 --> 46:26.575
[clanging]

46:27.868 --> 46:29.703
I'm flush with relics.

46:29.786 --> 46:30.788
[clatters]

46:30.871 --> 46:31.747
Nobody wants 'em.

46:33.457 --> 46:36.335
Got anything from Earth?

46:41.423 --> 46:43.258
- That a real Sol pendant?

46:44.384 --> 46:47.054
- Yeah. It's not mine, though.

46:47.137 --> 46:48.680
Belonged to a Mithraic soldier.

46:48.764 --> 46:51.099
- Whom I dispatched while
defending our settlement.

46:52.226 --> 46:54.645
- Well, if you're willing
to part with it,

46:54.728 --> 46:56.855
I'll give you 5 gallons
of fuel blood.

47:07.407 --> 47:08.992
- No.

47:09.076 --> 47:11.161
His possessions
are not on offer.

47:11.245 --> 47:12.621
Come on, Hunter.

47:12.704 --> 47:14.164
We'll find it somewhere else.

47:15.916 --> 47:18.001
[tools clanging]

47:18.085 --> 47:20.420
- Hold up.

47:24.925 --> 47:27.010
You said you dispatched people.

47:28.554 --> 47:30.222
You wanna fight Billy?

47:30.305 --> 47:31.431
[bystanders cheering]

47:31.515 --> 47:33.058
Should he fight Billy?

47:33.141 --> 47:35.561
all: Yeah!

47:35.644 --> 47:37.187
- No, no, no, no, no.
He can't fight anybody.

47:37.271 --> 47:38.772
He's already damaged.

47:38.855 --> 47:40.232
- Fight?
- Mm-mm.

47:40.315 --> 47:42.442
- In the sporting sense?
- Mm-hmm.

47:42.526 --> 47:47.072
In the sense that you
have to knock him down...

47:47.155 --> 47:50.075
before he knocks you down.

47:51.326 --> 47:53.412
- Hmm.

47:53.495 --> 47:54.371
[crowd cheering]

47:54.454 --> 47:56.039
- Fight, fight, fight!

47:56.123 --> 47:59.376
[cheering]

48:00.335 --> 48:02.337
[tense music]

48:02.421 --> 48:05.882
[crowd cheering]

48:05.966 --> 48:07.342
- [laughs]

48:07.426 --> 48:10.262
[indistinct chatter]

48:10.345 --> 48:12.097
- Try and take out his senses
as fast as you can.

48:12.180 --> 48:13.390
Hey, hey, hey.

48:13.473 --> 48:14.224
With your injuries,
you can't afford for things

48:14.308 --> 48:16.768
to go longer
than a few minutes, okay?

48:16.852 --> 48:18.228
- Father?

48:18.979 --> 48:21.106
Was this your idea?
- No.

48:21.189 --> 48:21.940
What the hell
are you doing here?

48:22.024 --> 48:25.110
Who's this idiot?
- He's a friend of mine.

48:25.193 --> 48:25.611
- You know she's Mithraic,
right?

48:25.694 --> 48:26.778
- This guy the father?

48:29.156 --> 48:30.282
- Bring out Billy!

48:30.365 --> 48:32.492
[crowd cheering]

48:32.576 --> 48:35.913
[heavy mechanical footsteps]

48:35.996 --> 48:38.123
[saw buzzes]

48:38.206 --> 48:40.083
- Oh, shit.
That's an industrial.

48:40.167 --> 48:41.627
You can't fight an industrial.

48:41.710 --> 48:43.545
- I'm less afraid
of an unintelligent machine.

48:43.629 --> 48:46.423
- That thing will destroy you.

48:46.506 --> 48:48.258
- Wait, wait, wait.
Take this.

48:50.719 --> 48:53.055
- An unnecessary accessory.

48:53.138 --> 48:54.556
- You said you wanted to win,
didn't you?

48:56.558 --> 48:57.309
Go get him, Pop.

48:57.392 --> 48:59.936
[sighs] You got this.

49:01.355 --> 49:04.107
[crowd shouting]

49:06.234 --> 49:08.320
[chainsaw buzzes]

49:08.403 --> 49:09.821
[cheering]

49:09.905 --> 49:10.155
- You got this, Pop.

49:10.238 --> 49:12.157
- Fight!

49:12.240 --> 49:13.533
- Come on. Come on. Come on.

49:13.617 --> 49:15.577
[bell dings]
- Fight!

49:15.661 --> 49:18.538
[cheering]

49:18.622 --> 49:21.541
[bullets firing rapidly]

49:21.625 --> 49:23.335
[shouting, cheering]

49:23.418 --> 49:26.338
[metal clanging]

49:27.589 --> 49:30.258
[chainsaw buzzing]

49:33.428 --> 49:34.179
[cheering]

49:34.262 --> 49:35.180
- Whoo!

49:35.263 --> 49:37.349
- [grunting]

49:37.432 --> 49:38.517
[crowd exclaims]

49:38.600 --> 49:40.477
- You got this, Pop!

49:40.560 --> 49:42.104
- Come on. Come on.

49:42.187 --> 49:43.313
- Father, watch out!

49:43.397 --> 49:44.523
[chainsaw buzzes]

49:44.606 --> 49:46.233
- That's it! That's it!

49:46.316 --> 49:48.443
[clanging]

49:48.527 --> 49:50.195
You got it! You got it!
You got it!

49:50.278 --> 49:52.572
- [grunting]

49:52.656 --> 49:53.949
- Yeah!

49:54.032 --> 49:55.367
- [laughs]

49:55.450 --> 49:56.535
- Come on.

49:56.618 --> 49:58.537
[chainsaw buzzing]

49:58.620 --> 50:01.123
- [grunts]
- Bash him, Pop!

50:01.206 --> 50:02.499
Let's get him, Pop!

50:02.582 --> 50:04.209
[chainsaw buzzes]

50:04.292 --> 50:05.711
[mechanical stuttering]

50:05.794 --> 50:06.712
- Yeah!

50:06.795 --> 50:08.171
- [shouts]

50:08.255 --> 50:09.631
- That's it, Pop!

50:09.715 --> 50:10.465
[mechanical stuttering]

50:10.549 --> 50:13.385
[crowd cheering]

50:13.468 --> 50:16.388
- [grunts]

50:16.471 --> 50:19.182
[crowd cheering]

50:19.266 --> 50:19.683
- Let's go, Pop!

50:19.766 --> 50:22.310
Let's go! Let's go!

50:22.394 --> 50:24.438
You did it! You did it!
You did it!

50:24.521 --> 50:25.564
That's it! That's it!

50:25.647 --> 50:29.234
Money! Money! Let's go!

50:29.317 --> 50:32.404
[wind gusting]

50:33.739 --> 50:36.783
[waves crashing]

50:49.004 --> 50:50.922
- In your presence,
everything is brighter

50:51.006 --> 50:52.966
and more glorious,
your eminence,

50:53.049 --> 50:54.426
- We're not doing
"your eminence" anymore.

50:54.509 --> 50:57.262
- Captain Drusus.

50:59.014 --> 51:00.766
- And no more last name.

51:02.142 --> 51:05.020
We're all part
of the same family now.

51:05.103 --> 51:06.605
[high-pitched tone]

51:06.688 --> 51:09.566
- As you wish, Marcus.

51:15.655 --> 51:19.326
[ominous music]

51:19.409 --> 51:25.582
♪ ♪

51:25.665 --> 51:26.458
- What are we waiting for?

51:26.541 --> 51:29.044
- Just not sure
we should be doing this.

51:38.345 --> 51:39.805
- Mm.

51:39.888 --> 51:42.974
- The scales trap
the heat of the sun.

51:43.058 --> 51:46.394
So I can draw on Sol's power
even at night.

51:47.437 --> 51:50.065
- Hmm.

51:50.148 --> 51:53.068
[soft music]

51:53.151 --> 51:59.199
♪ ♪

52:06.915 --> 52:08.416
[laughs]

52:15.090 --> 52:18.969
♪ ♪

52:19.052 --> 52:21.429
- Let's go back.
This is a bad idea.

52:21.513 --> 52:23.056
- Paul?

52:27.727 --> 52:29.980
- Don't. Paul, don't.

52:30.063 --> 52:32.524
[intense music]

52:32.607 --> 52:34.526
- Paulie?

52:35.610 --> 52:36.862
It's okay.

52:36.945 --> 52:38.196
You and your friends
are welcome.

52:38.280 --> 52:39.114
Come on.

52:39.197 --> 52:42.200
- [breathing heavily]

52:42.284 --> 52:49.040
♪ ♪

52:54.629 --> 52:58.174
[wind gusting]

52:58.258 --> 52:59.968
[waves crashing]

53:00.051 --> 53:02.137
[high-pitched tone]

53:06.641 --> 53:09.603
[ominous music]

53:09.686 --> 53:16.735
♪ ♪
